titles: An elegy humbly offered to the memory of the Reverend Father in God Doctor Humphry Henchman, late Bishop of London, who departed this life the 8th of October 1675.
notes: Verse: "Stand off, you Common Vouchers for the Dead ..."
Within mourning border, with emblems and motto at head.
Reproduction of original in the British Library.
keywords: Henchman, Humphrey, 1592-1675 --  Poetry --  Early works to 1800.
